result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Christopher D Nell was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Collections may include income assignment.

Defendant Christopher D Nell in court, in custody, with attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Catherine Siudzinski appeared as interpreter for the defendant's mother.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty. Count 2 and Count 3 are dismissed and read in. Count 4 is dismissed by operation of law.

Court orders the following: 
- Total sentence: 4 years (Initial Confinement: 2 years, Extended Supervision: 2 years) 73 days of credit
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 36 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 36 months Ignition Interlock on every vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant
- Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel meeting while on Extended Supervision
- Fine totaling: $1141.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision. 
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Waukesha Police Department
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision. 
- Conditions of Extended Supervision: Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs. No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription. Valid prescriptions to be taken in the manner they were prescribed and disclosed to Agent.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week and obtain a sponsor.  DNA Sample if not yet provided, defendant to pay surcharge.
